        {
          "role": "user",
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "What is the Eiffel Tower?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "role": "model",
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "The Eiffel Tower is a wrought-iron lattice tower on the Champ de Mars in Paris, France. It is one of the most recognizable structures in the world and a symbol of Paris.\n\nHere's a bit more about it:\n\n*   **Purpose:** Originally built as the entrance arch to the 1889 World's Fair.\n*   **Designer:** Gustave Eiffel's company designed and built it.\n*   **Height:** Approximately 330 meters (1,083 feet) tall, including the antenna.\n*   **Construction:** It took just over two years to build (1887-1889).\n*   **Tourism:** It is one of the most visited paid monuments in the world, attracting millions of visitors each year.\n*   **Features:** It has three levels for visitors, with restaurants on the first and second levels. The top level's upper platform is the highest accessible to the public in the European Union.\n\nIn short, it's a famous and iconic landmark, known for its distinctive design, height, and historical significance."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "role": "user",
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "When was it built?"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "role": "model",
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "The Eiffel Tower was built from **1887 to 1889**. Construction started on January 28, 1887, and it was completed on March 31, 1889.\n"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "role": "user",
          "parts": [
            {
              "text": "How tall is it?"
            }
          ]
        }
      ],
